  <h2 class="text-balance">Problems with Starting a Blog and their Solutions</h2>
  <p>Even as competition increases, people still want to learn how to start a blog. The problem is getting traffic and views that will lead to opportunities. </p>
  
  Some of these opportunities are:
  <ul>
  <li>job hunting </li>
    <li>establishing yourself as an expert</li>
      <li>communicating about a hobby</li>
        <li>starting a small business </li>
          <li>making money as a professional blogger.</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p>Traditionally, one would approach this through content marketing. A fancy word for blogging to get search traffic. That converts to subscribers or customers. That is getting increasingly difficult. Search Engine Optimization can not be your only way to get traffic. There is a better way through community building and outreach. </p> 
  
 <p>The point of this blog is to give you the advice you need to get started today. Explain the benefits for you and how to achieve them. You will be learning alongside a whole community of writers. </p>
  
  <p>You don’t have to start your blog alone. My aim is to provide a safe space for you to learn and connect with others. Growing together and offering support.</p> 
  
  <p>To this end, I’ve created a <a href="https://bloggingbuds.com"></a>newsletter called the Blogging Buds</a>. Each week, we have a community spotlight so that we can share and discuss what we have written. There are future planned activities like a monthly blog challenge and a comment hour. </p>
  
  <p>You will also receive updates on published articles from the blog. </p>
  
  <p>So, what are these elusive benefits of starting a blog? They are numerous and surprising. I’m proud of the recognition and achievements that I’ve had over my career. I want to help you reach your goals and find blogging success. </p>
