<h2 class="text-balance">Benefits of Starting a Blog</h2>


<p>
In the first section, we mentioned five motivations that you may have for starting a blog. Let’s tackle each of these in order from writing for views to writing for money. Either of these goals is worth the time that it takes to write. 
</p>
<h3>Writing About a Hobby</h3>


<p>
Hobbies are something specific to every individual. Not everyone shares our interests. I’ve personally faced a lot of rejection over my love of mathematics. There are people out there who feel the way that I do. But, they are not necessarily people in my personal life. So, writing gives me an outlet to talk about my passion. Something that has led to <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/hessiejones/2023/08/25/empowering-confidence-overcoming-math-anxiety-in-the-age-of-artificial-intelligence/?sh=9cc38317e2c2">co-authoring an article for the Forbes website</a>. 
</p>
<h3>Establishing Expertise</h3>


<p>
It isn’t uncommon for someone to want to write a blog to establish their expertise. That is often referred to as through leadership. It is a way to network with other people in your industry. Some people even go on to be influencers. It is a lucrative position if you can build your following and a blog is one way to do that. This can lead to opportunities like public speaking. Or publishing books about your experiences. 
</p>
<h3>Professional Networking</h3>


<p>
A blog makes it easier to network with others by starting conversations. Outreach is key to building a community and a professional network. This has led to every job opportunity in my life. People get to know you through your writing. Their referrals give you a way to get in the door at a company and in front of hiring managers. Blogging facilitates the building of these relationships even though it does take time. 
</p>
<h3>Starting a Small Business</h3>


<p>
Content marketing is one way to bring people to your website. In this method, you use your blog to get search engine traffic that leads to purchases. You can turn your hobby into profit if you are clever about it. I used to sell math cross stitch on Etsy. My blog was a way of promoting that work. Now, I offer all my patterns for free. 
</p>
<h3>Professional Blogging</h3>


<p>
Some writers make money directly from blogging. There are several ways to do this. Like selling digital products, merch, or using affiliate links. Other methods are advertising like writing sponsored posts. Building trust with your audience is essential. As well as establishing expertise in your topic. Both of these will convince others that what you offer is trustworthy. 
</p>
